The music Eswatini composed both ethnic Swazi music and varieties folk music well modern genres such rock pop and hip hop which has been popular Swaziland since the headed bands such Vamoose The popularity hip hop South Africa which shares border with Swaziland has also helped popularize Two major festivals the country are Incwala and Umhlanga The former takes place December while the latter takes place August Umhlanga known for its dance performed exclusively women and its 5day ceremony which involves reedcutting Traditional instruments used include the kudu horn calabash rattles makeyana and reed flute 